  <recipe>
    <head>
      <title>Apple-Raisin Stuffing</title>
      <categories>
        <cat>None</cat></categories>
      <yield>1</yield></head>
    <ingredients>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1</qty>
          <unit>cup</unit></amt>
        <item>Chopped celery</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1</qty>
          <unit>cup</unit></amt>
        <item>Chopped onion</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>2</qty>
          <unit>tablespoons</unit></amt>
        <item>Butter or margarine</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>3</qty>
          <unit>cups</unit></amt>
        <item>Chopped peeled apples</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>2</qty>
          <unit>cups</unit></amt>
        <item>Raisins</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>8</qty>
          <unit>cups</unit></amt>
        <item>Cubed day-old white bread</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>2</qty>
          <unit>tablespoons</unit></amt>
        <item>Sugar (up to 3)</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1</qty>
          <unit>teaspoon</unit></amt>
        <item>Salt</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>2</qty>
          <unit/></amt>
        <item>Eggs</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1/2</qty>
          <unit>cups</unit></amt>
        <item>Apple cider</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1/2</qty>
          <unit>cups</unit></amt>
        <item>Water</item></ing></ingredients>
    <directions>
      <step>  (From Taste of Home Oct./Nov. 1996 by Denise Goedeken Platte Center,
  Nebraska).  This recipe was shown served with roasted goose...however I'm
  going to make it with turkey.
  
  In a skillet, saute the celery and onion in butter; transfer to a large
  bowl. Add the apples, raisins, bread, sugar and salt. In a small bowl, beat
  eggs, cider and water. Pour over bread mixture and toss lightly. Stuff your
  turkey (says goose 10-12 pounds).
